HEADWORD: Urodela
<hw>U`ro*de"la</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL.; Gr.
<?/ tail + <?/ visible.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>An order of
amphibians having the tail well developed and often long. It comprises
the salamanders, tritons, and allied animals.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

